CHATBOT
overview-the main explanation
A simple AI chatbot built with Python Flask as the backend and JavaScript/HTML as the frontend.  
It accepts user messages, sends them to the Flask API, and returns AI-generated responses using OpenAI’s API.

Features
Flask backend API for chat responses
Frontend chat UI using vanilla JS
Connects to OpenAI models (GPT‑type)
Spotify API integration

Technologies Used
- Python  
- Flask  
- JavaScript  +++
- HTML / CSS  
- Spotipy for Spotify API  
- Supabase client  
- OpenAI’s API

Required stuff to download so it works the way it should
Python 3.x
OpenAI API key
Spotify API credentials
Supabase credentials

Installation
git clone https://github.com/tumo-hasmik/Chatbot.git
cd Chatbot
Create Python environment!
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # or venv\Scripts\activate on Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt

Running the app
python example.py   || if it doesn't work you can try python3!!

Environment Variables
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET
OPENAI_API_KEY
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY

Example Usage
You double click on index.html and open it in the browser,then ask my Melody AI everything you want(music) and she answers you!!